This paper is primarily focused on improving language modelling, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks and hyperparameter tuning, which are common topics in machine learning. This suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for language modelling, which falls under the category of computer vision (CV), making cs.CV a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses noise-contrastive estimation (NCE), which is a statistical method, suggesting that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
